<br>
1) Mask of the Wurms isn't bad either<br>
<br>
2) In my regular groups we have a ranger pull.  I usually stand 10-20 feet in front of the group.  After the puller says &quot;INC&quot;, I starting hitting the heal button until he is in range.  The heal hits him as he runs by me.  The mob he pulled keeps following him to the group; and the rest all aggro onto me.  The chanter then mezzes the ones hitting me; then I rejoin the fight.<br>
<br>
This tactic does a couple things.<br>
A) It gives the puller a few more HP before the cleric would need to get aggro.<br>
B) It keeps the extra mobs away from the group and battle.<br>
C) It usually keeps the extra mobs spread out enough so the chanters can easily select them for re-mezzing.  Because when he starts to mez, I move a few feet to spread them apart.<br>
<br>
Pudg <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ubeldukil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beldukil</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.greycouncil.org/members/beldukil/untitled.gif height=27 width=16 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 2419<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/12/00 1:55:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathtomesofknowledge.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/gwlaw99/beldpic1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Short Guide to the 50+ Paladin</span><hr size=1> Good pulling tip Pudge, I do that as well.  I will also incorporate the taunting and stunning before breaking mez as well. <p><BR>
